snippet.textDisplay: i could not imagine being in your shoes....im so sensitive about my weight. in 2015 i lost over 80lb i was working out EVERYDAY and was eating very little. it wasn't a healthy way to lose weight but i lost the weight so who cares right? anyway prior to this i never had any males have any interest in me, i was constant third wheel and lacked confidence. the weight lost changed that, i felt actually pretty for once... well i felt NOT ugly and that was close to pretty. See I've always hated my body....life ACTUAL hate the disgust i would feel when i would look at myself in a mirror  was felt in my core... i would want to hit myself or inflict pain (i never did) but that's how much i could not stand the site of myself. After the weight loss i felt so proud of myself. Clothes fit right, i could exercise comfortably i gained confidence and eventually met my now husband. They say you gain weight when you fall in love and i can attest to that, i fell in love for the first time and the weight started creeping back on. i had thought i hated myself before but boooooyyyyyyy lemme tell ya i didn't even know the definition.  as the pounds kept coming the disgust swept over, i would stare at myself in the mirror and  say awful things to myself. "You stupid fat B*tch"  "You ugly fat pig" and those where the nicer descriptions. it got so bad i couldn't even look at my reflection, in mirrors in windows i avoided myself. My clothes started getting tight and i just continued to eat. food was my comfort,  even as a kid i use to get in trouble for eating TOO MUCH. i would hide candy bars and snacks and eat them before i got home. I've always had an unhealthy relationship with food, and because im over weight people where allowed to comment on it.... "your gaining weight again you might want to slow down on eating" "Oh wow have you thought about going back to the gym?"  What these helpful people dont understand is I KNOW. i know its not healthy, i know its not normal, i know im fat and for whatever reason that makes you so concerned that you have to give me helpful advise. i KNOW. then i had my daughter and DAMMMIITTT i gained more weight. So here i am 5 years later and im fat again i try not to hate myself because i have a beautiful little girl who needs to have confidence instilled in her......but its hard because i know once i lose it again everyone going to say "You look so good!" "Wow you LOST ALOT of weight good for you!" and i'll be reminded that i am disgusting when im fat and only NOT UGLY when the weight is off.....

snippet.textDisplay: You are such a beautiful soul with such an amazing spirit. It's 2020 and its truly sad that fat shaming is still a thing. I am 25 and have four children that my weight between having babies and getting an umbilical hernia I literally felt like i was a walking blob (like from the R.L.Stine The BLOB). I cared more about what people thought about me than I should have. My depression and anxiety got so bad that i just curled up in a blanket burrito and hoped that i would die. It wasnt until my 6 year old son came to me fat shaming himself. Started running none stop and wouldnt eat. He is 6. I realized how much me feeling and thinking I looked like lumpy space Princess and Flubber had a baby, which was me, had effected my son. We dont realize whos watching until its too late. I never wanted my kids to feel like i do everyday. Disgusting. I have watched you since the beginning of your career. I loved your hair and your personality which after awhile i found myself having to watch your videos to be able to get through the day. Like no matter how bad you were having it you made jokes through it all and it got me motivated to roll and lose my breath to get out of bed. You are literally my spirit animal. Aside from pigs because they are my everything, but you have been through so much in your life and overcame so many obstacles that youre a freaking inspiration! You have a loving fiance who obviously adores you and you have so many supporters, i really hope you are taking care of you, mentally. Its easy to say who gives fuck about the haters, but when you are literally a YouTube God i know it takes a toll on you having to see the trolls and drama channels discussing you and your body. P.S mfs it costs 0.00 to mind your own mf business!  "LEAVE SHANE ALONE!!!"  *In Chris Crocker voice*. Shane you are Gorgeous in every way! You wont see this comment which is okay, but i know someone who is going through what you are will and know that they are boss ass bitches and love the skin your in! If someone calls you fat scream like a pterodactyl at them. Why? Because why tf not!
